                            <comment id="12955089" author="frolovmx" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 13:38:18 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Bug in &lt;em&gt;weld-core-impl&lt;/em&gt;-2.1.2.Final?&lt;br/&gt;
The &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/weld/core/blob/2.1.2.Final/impl/src/main/java/org/jboss/weld/xml/BeansXmlHandler.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;BeansXmlHandler&lt;/a&gt; always calls interpolate(), even if the argument is &lt;em&gt;null&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
At runtime Wildfly calls interpolate() method which is overridden by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/wildfly/wildfly/blob/8.0.0.Final/weld/src/main/java/org/jboss/as/weld/deployment/PropertyReplacingBeansXmlHandler.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;PropertyReplacingBeansXmlHandler&lt;/a&gt;, which delegates processing to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jboss/metadata/blob/8.0.0.Final/common/src/main/java/org/jboss/metadata/property/DefaultPropertyReplacer.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;DefaultPropertyReplacer&lt;/a&gt;. Nowehere the null-check is performed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think, that the BeansXmlHandler should not call interpolate() method at all if the value of attribute or XML element is absent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12955100" author="frolovmx" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 13:58:47 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I asked in WELD-DEV mailing list (&lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.jboss.org/pipermail/weld-dev/2014-March/003224.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://lists.jboss.org/pipermail/weld-dev/2014-March/003224.html&lt;/a&gt;), whether this issue might be a bug in &lt;em&gt;weld-core-impl&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
